messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /admin/register

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The AdminController class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so method-level mappings are absolute.
- The newAdmin(...) handler is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/admin/register", method = RequestMethod.POST). That explicitly binds the endpoint to the path "/admin/register" and only the HTTP POST method.
- There are no annotations in the code that allow other methods (no mappings with no method attribute, no RequestMethod.GET/PUT/DELETE/PATCH/HEAD/OPTIONS/TRACE). Per the instruction to base decisions on the code (not runtime framework behavior), only POST is acceptable.
